explanation: No additional symbols are required. UtTest_Run has no formal parameters, so the MISRA rule “A function parameter should not be modified” cannot be violated by this function itself. Verifying called functions or type definitions (UtListNode_t, UtTestDataBaseEntry_t, UtAssert_Global, or the callees' implementations) is unnecessary to determine whether UtTest_Run modifies its own parameters, because there are none. If you instead want to check that any called function adheres to the same MISRA rule, then the implementations/prototypes of each callee (UT_BSP_Lock, UT_BSP_Unlock, UtList_GetHead, UtList_Merge, UtList_GetNext, UtList_GetObject, UtAssert_BeginTest, UtAssert_SetContext, UtAssert_EndTest, UtList_Destroy, UT_BSP_EndTest, UtAssert_GetCounters, plus the definitions of UtAssert_Global and the list/test-entry types) would be required.
